
# 📄 Payment Service Architecture & Flow Document
**Project:** Quick Commerce App (Zambia)
**Supported Methods:** Cash on Delivery (COD) & Airtel Money (STK Push)
**Status:** Updated to reflect final implemented design (v2)

---

## 1. Overview & Order State Machine

The user selects their payment method on the Cart/Checkout page. Order creation and payment initiation are **two separate API calls**, keeping order tracking reliable even if Airtel's API is temporarily slow or unavailable.

### Core Order States
| State | Description |
|---|---|
| `PENDING_PAYMENT` | Order created, inventory reserved. Waiting for payment. |
| `CONFIRMED` | Payment successful (or COD selected). Sent to store to pack. |
| `CANCELLED` | Payment failed/timed out, or user abandoned. Inventory released. `cancelledReason` field explains why (e.g. `PAYMENT_FAILED: TF`). |

> **Design decision:** There is no separate `PAYMENT_FAILED` state. A failed payment transitions the order directly to `CANCELLED` with a `cancelledReason`. This simplifies the state machine. The user is shown a "Try Again" option which creates a **new order** — there is no in-place retry for MVP.

