## 5. Edge Cases & Error Handling

| Case | Trigger | Backend Action | Frontend UX |
|---|---|---|---|
| **A. Failed payment** | Airtel webhook `TF`/`TA` | Order → `CANCELLED` with `cancelledReason` | "Payment not completed." → [Try Again] / [Use COD] |
| **B. User ignores PIN prompt** | No webhook + timeout | `AirtelFailsafeScheduler` queries Airtel after 60s | Prompt expired → [Try Again] / [Use COD] |
| **C. Lost webhook** | User paid but webhook missed | Failsafe scheduler detects `TS` from Airtel API → `CONFIRMED` | Next poll shows success |
| **D. User closes app** | App killed mid-flow | Backend still receives webhook → `CONFIRMED` | On reopen: `GET /active_orders` shows confirmed order → redirect to tracking |
| **E. Airtel API down at push time** | `/pay` returns error | Order left in `PENDING_PAYMENT`, cleanup scheduler cancels after timeout | "Couldn't reach Airtel." → [Use COD] |

